http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Tiruchirapalli/Tamilisai-Vizha-ends/article14006696.ece

The three-day 45th annual Tamilisai Vizha organised at Tiruvaiyaru under the auspices of the Tiruvaiyaru Tamilisai Mandram concluded at the Rajah’s College here on Sunday.Assistant Director of Art and Culture R. Gunasekaran offered felicitations. Mandram president Velu Maavaliyaar presided. Tiruvaiyaru MLA M. Rethinasamy inaugurated the proceedings. Thanjavur MLA M. Rengasamy and Papanasam MLA R. Duraikkannu were present.Carnatic music exponent Bombay Jayashree’s vocal concert, bharatanatyam performance by students of the Tiruvaiyaru Aadalvallan Natya Palli and Nadaswaram by Kalyanapuram Srinivasan embellished the first day’s proceedings while music concert by vocalist O.S. Arun, bharatanatyam by Chinnamanoor Sujatha and her troupe, “Tiruneelakanta Nayanar” drama penned, directed and led by Nidamangalam Gopalakrishnan stood out on the second day. Sri Arun was conferred the title “Pannisai Arasu” by the Mandram.On the third day, music concerts by Chennai Gayatri Venkatraman, debate and a cultural folk art programme enlivened the events.